    <div class="AssessmentProblem.type">RestrictedConstructedResponse</div>
    <div class="AssessmentProblem.statement"><p>A caterer needs to buy 21 pounds of pasta to cater a wedding. At a local store, 8 pounds of pasta cost&#xA0;<span>$</span>12. How much will the caterer pay for the pasta there?</p>

<ol>
	<li>Write a ratio for the given information about the cost of pasta.<presentation-tag data-tag-title="HALF INCH" data-tree-code="MS_pi" data-tree-node-id="243962" data-tree-ref-id="215" src="/presentation_tags/3.tag"></presentation-tag><presentation-tag data-tag-title="HALF INCH" data-tree-code="Accel6_8" data-tree-node-id="260635" data-tree-ref-id="218" src="/presentation_tags/3.tag"></presentation-tag>
</li>
	<li>Would it be more helpful to write an equivalent ratio with 1 pound of pasta as one of the numbers, or with <span>$</span>1 as one of the numbers? Explain your reasoning, and then write that equivalent ratio.<presentation-tag data-tag-title="HALF INCH" data-tree-code="MS_pi" data-tree-node-id="243962" data-tree-ref-id="215" src="/presentation_tags/3.tag"></presentation-tag><presentation-tag data-tag-title="HALF INCH" data-tree-code="Accel6_8" data-tree-node-id="260635" data-tree-ref-id="218" src="/presentation_tags/3.tag"></presentation-tag>
</li>
	<li>Find the answer and explain or show your reasoning.&#xA0;<presentation-tag data-tag-title="HALF INCH" data-tree-code="MS_pi" data-tree-node-id="243962" data-tree-ref-id="215" src="/presentation_tags/3.tag"></presentation-tag><presentation-tag data-tag-title="HALF INCH" data-tree-code="Accel6_8" data-tree-node-id="260635" data-tree-ref-id="218" src="/presentation_tags/3.tag"></presentation-tag>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
    <div class="AssessmentProblem.solution"><ol>
	<li>Answers vary. Sample responses: <span>$</span>12 for every 8 pounds;&#xA0;&#xA0;<span>$</span>12 to 8&#xA0;pounds; 8 pounds to <span>$</span>12.</li>
	<li>Answers vary. Sample response: Finding 1 pound would be easier and more helpful. The cost of 1 pound can be easily found by dividing <span>$</span>12 by 8 and the result (the unit rate) can be multiplied by 21. The ratio is $1.50 to 1 pound.&#xA0;</li>
	<li>
<span>$</span>31.50. Possible reasonings: <span class="math math-repaired" data-png-file-id="failed-conversion">\(21 \boldcdot (1.50) =&#xA0;&#xA0;31.50\)</span>.&#xA0;
